{{Infobox journal | title = Iran and the Caucasus | cover = | discipline = | abbreviation = Iran Cauc. | editor = Garnik S. Asatrian | publisher = [[Brill Publishers]] in collaboration with the Caucasian Centre for Iranian Studies ([[Yerevan]]) | country = Iran | frequency = Biannual | history = 1997–present | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.brill.nl/ic | link1 = http://booksandjournals.brillonline.com/content/journals/1573384x | link1-name = Online archive | link2 = | link2-name = | ISSN = 1609-8498 | eISSN = 1573-384X | OCLC = 233145721 | LCCN = 2001227055 | JSTOR = 16098498 }} '''''Iran and the Caucasus''''' is a biannual [[multidisciplinarity|multidisciplinary]] [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Brill Publishers]] in collaboration with the Caucasian Centre for Iranian Studies ([[Yerevan]]). The journal covers the history (ancient, mediaeval and modern), culture, anthropology, literature (textology), folklore, linguistics, archaeology, politics, and economy of the region. Articles are published in English, French and German. It was established in 1997 by [[:w:fa:گارنیک آساتوریان|Garnik Asatrian]], the head of the Center.<ref>[http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/iran-and-the-caucasus Victoria Arakelova, "Iran and the Caucasus" in Encyclopaedia Iranica]</ref> The [[editor-in-chief]] is Garnik S. Asatrian ([[Yerevan]]).
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index]] and the [[International Bibliography of the Social Sciences]].
