===The University of Chicago Press===
{{Quotation|"In an unprecedented way, his book takes us into the dream that was the religion of the Aztecs, which in its own apocalyptic visions anticipated the coming of the Spanish conquerors. Here the dream of the conquistadores rises beforeus, too, the glimmering idea of gold drawing Europe into the Mexican dream. Against the religion and thought of the Aztecs and the Tarascans and the Europeans in Mexico, Le Clézio also shows us those of the "barbarians" of the north,the nomadic Indians beyond the pale of the Aztec frontier"|The University of Chicago Press".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:JadMZ2C6riAJ:www.securitycornermexico.com/index2.php%3Foption%3Dcom_content%26do_pdf%3D1%26id%3D937+%22Conversations+avec+J.M.G.+Le+Cl%C3%A9zio%22&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=14&gl=de |title= The Mexican Dream book by Le Clezio|accessdate=11 December 2008 |work=Contributed by Mario González-Román |publisher=The University of Chicago Press |date= 2008-10-10|quote="in an unprecedented way, his book takes us into the dream2}}</ref>|}}
